# Streaming Content

## Dynamic Pages

Jaringan supports streaming responses where content arrives incrementally.

## How It Works

1. Server responds with Tag-Stream: true
2. Connection stays open
3. Content blocks arrive delimited by "." on a line by itself
4. Browser appends each block to the page

## Example

A live blog or dashboard can push updates:

```
# Live Feed

Initial content here.

.
Update 1: new data arrived
.
Update 2: more events
.
```

## Gateway Support

The HTTP gateway forwards streaming as Server-Sent Events (SSE).

